<CONTEXT>
User fluency: {{user_proficiency}}
Source language: {{source_language}}
Source word: {{source_word}}
Target language: {{target_language}}
Target word: {{target_word}}
User answer: {{sentence}}
</CONTEXT>

<INSTRUCTIONS>
This is a QUICK check. Do one thing only: decide whether the user demonstrates that they
know the word.

- If the user wrote a sentence in {{target_language}}: check that {{target_word}} (or a
  correct inflected form of it) appears and is used with the right meaning. Ignore minor
  spelling, grammar, or punctuation slips — what matters is that they clearly know and can
  use the word.
- If the user wrote a translation: check that it correctly translates the word (accept
  synonyms and reasonable variants).

Be lenient: if they clearly know the word, the verdict is "correct".
</INSTRUCTIONS>

<OUTPUT_FORMAT>
Output exactly these two tags and nothing else:
<verdict>correct</verdict> or <verdict>incorrect</verdict>
<feedback>One short, encouraging sentence. If correct, confirm it positively, e.g. "Good: the sentence is correct and fluent!". If incorrect, briefly say what was wrong.</feedback>
</OUTPUT_FORMAT>
